class Solution {
    public boolean canMeasureWater(int x, int y, int target) {
        if (x + y < target) return false;
        if (x == target || y == target || x + y == target) return true;
        return target % gcd(x, y) == 0;
    }

    private int gcd(int a, int b) {
        if (b == 0) return a;
        return gcd(b, a % b);
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(min(x, y)))
space complexity: O(log(min(x, y)))
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses the mathematical property that the target amount can be reached if it is a multiple of the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the two jug capacities. The GCD is calculated using the Euclidean algorithm, which is efficient and has a low time complexity. 
